x 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2,\"repo\":\"iboyperson/p9k-theme-pastel\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A theme for the <a href=\"https://github.com/romkatv/powerlevel10k\">powerlevel10k</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/romkatv/powerlevel10k\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">17.4k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":17354,\"repo\":\"romkatv/powerlevel10k\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> prompt that puts an emphasis on simplcity while still getting important information across.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T16:21:45.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Product Management</h2><h3>Product Strategy</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>Windows Vista as a prime example of a <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SwiftOnSecurity/status/851861076429991937\">sacrificial lamb product</a>: a massive unpopular re-architecture required to pave the way for future innovative release. That's the cautionary tale of why you should be ready for intense criticism and adversity, if by chance or fate your wander down the path of monumental changes in a business software.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T16:12:12.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Roles</h2><h3>Engineering Managers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.intercom.com/blog/great-product-managers-dont-spend-time-on-solutions/\">Great PMs don't spend their time on solutions</a> - Not on solutions, no. But on customer's problems.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:49:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Project Management</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/hackernoon/lets-have-no-managers-instead-of-managers-with-no-engineering-experience-e8b7cd29d398\">Let's have no managers, instead of managers with no engineering experience</a> - The title is misleading, article's argument is: we don't need <em>project</em> managers if we already have <em>product</em> managers and scrum masters.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:49:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Objectives and Key Results (OKR)</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://zafulabs.com/2019/05/24/okrs-from-a-development-teams-perspective/\">OKRs from a development team's perspective</a> - On how OKRs articulates with a backlog.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:49:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Objectives and Key Results (OKR)</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://hrblog.spotify.com/2016/08/15/our-beliefs/\">Why individual OKRs don't work for us</a> - Spotify decision to stop using OKRs for individuals.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:49:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Engineering to Management Transition</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>You always been a developer. Being offered <a href=\"https://fractio.nl/2014/09/19/not-a-promotion-a-career-change/\">a management position is not a promotion. It is a change in career</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Engineering to Management Transition</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://charity.wtf/2019/09/08/reasons-not-to-be-a-manager/\">17 Reasons not to be a Manager</a> - An article to <a href=\"https://youtu.be/b07887ZzKiw?t=40\">discourage the faint-hearted recruits</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Engineering to Management Transition</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://twitter.com/ValaAfshar/status/966125964861280256\">Advice to new managers</a> - 9 fundamental principles of the behavior required to be a great manager.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Engineering to Management Transition</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=18823616\">Going from Developer to Manager. What should I know or learn?</a></li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Engineering to Management Transition</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://getweeklyupdate.com/manager-guide\">How to be a Manager – A step-by-step guide to leading a team</a> - A full, detailed guide on modern management practices.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Building Teams</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.elidedbranches.com/2016/11/building-and-motivating-engineering.html\">Building and Motivating Engineering Teams</a> - What DO engineers want? Money, purpose and respect.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Roles</h2><h3>Executives</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://twitter.com/kdeldycke/status/1088001688722644992\">Executives ratify decisions made on the spot</a> - Refines the concept above adapting <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=18089716\">Tolstoy's thesis to business</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Roles</h2><h3>Executives</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://fas.org/irp/doddir/army/adp6_22.pdf\">Army Leadership and the Profession</a> - Establishes and describes what leaders should be and do.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Roles</h2><h3>Executives</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://leadership.au.af.mil/sls-skil.htm\">US Air Force's Strategic Leadership Studies</a> - A reference of leadership's competencies and skills.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Roles</h2><h3>Executives</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://hbr.org/2018/07/the-leaders-calendar\">How CEOs Manage Time</a> - A study on what CEO of large companies spent their time on, and how. Opens a new window into what leadership is all about and into its many components and dimensions.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Roles</h2><h3>Executives</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.sametab.com/blog/operations-and-internal-communication-strategies-for-effective-ceos\">Operations and Internal Communication Strategies For Effective CEOs</a> - After insisting on the importance of context and narratives, the author provide an interesting template (good for inspiration) of ritual and recurring internal communication devices.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Roles</h2><h3>Engineering Managers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://rework.withgoogle.com/guides/managers-identify-what-makes-a-great-manager/steps/learn-about-googles-manager-research/\">Identify what makes a great manager</a> - Google tried to prove managers don't matter. Instead, it discovered <a href=\"https://www.inc.com/scott-mautz/google-tried-to-prove-managers-dont-matter-instead-they-discovered-10-traits-of-very-best-ones.html\">10 Traits of the Very Best Ones</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Roles</h2><h3>Engineering Managers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://twitter.com/johncutlefish/status/1124938723093766144\">As a product manager, how do you earn the respect and trust of your team?</a></li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Roles</h2><h3>Engineering Managers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://minnenratta.wordpress.com/2017/01/25/things-i-have-learnt-as-the-software-engineering-lead-of-a-multinational/\">Things I have learnt as the software engineering lead of a multinational</a> - Some interesting points here, some others needs to be challenged.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Recruitment</h2><h3>Interview</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/arialdomartini/Back-End-Developer-Interview-Questions\">Back-End Developer Interview Questions</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/arialdomartini/Back-End-Developer-Interview-Questions\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">11.3k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":11315,\"repo\":\"arialdomartini/Back-End-Developer-Interview-Questions\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A great source of inspiration.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Recruitment</h2><h3>Interview</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/viraptor/reverse-interview\">Reverse interview</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/viraptor/reverse-interview\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">17.1k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":17064,\"repo\":\"viraptor/reverse-interview\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Questions to ask the company during your interview. Be prepared to answer them as a manager.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Motivation</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u6XAPnuFjJc\">Drive: The surprising truth about what motivates us</a> - Daniel Pink summarizes it concisely: people are motivated by autonomy, mastery and purpose.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Culture</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/dwmkerr/hacker-laws\">hacker-laws</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/dwmkerr/hacker-laws\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">17.5k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":17521,\"repo\":\"dwmkerr/hacker-laws\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Laws, Theories, Principles and Patterns that developers will find useful.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Culture</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://people.clas.ufl.edu/ulan/files/Conrad.pdf\">Adaptation vs adaptability</a> - There is a spectrum between perfect efficiency and being completely flexible. This article explores ecosystems and the flows of material and energy between different organisms within the ecosystem. (<a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=20963513\">hinted by HN comment</a>)</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cognitive Tools</h2><h3>Collections</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@yegg/mental-models-i-find-repeatedly-useful-936f1cc405d#.qb3gkdmtk\">Mental Models I Find Repeatedly Useful</a> - Huge compiled list of mental models. Became the basis of book.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cognitive Tools</h2><h3>Explaining</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regression_toward_the_mean\">Regression toward the mean</a> - Or why after a period of intense euphoria and ambition, things slowly get back to their usual mediocrity.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Team Dynamics</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/cIQ36Kt7UVg?t=203\">A conversation with Elon Musk about Starship</a> - In a team with very talented contributors, everyone's is a chief engineer: you are expected to challenge the status-quo and questions other department's constraints. This allow smart engineers to avoid the trap of optimizing for something that should not exist in the first place.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Team Dynamics</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://courses.washington.edu/psii101/Powerpoints/Symptoms%20of%20Groupthink.htm\">Symptoms of Groupthink</a> - Overconfidence, tunnel vision and conformity pressure can led a group astray.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Team Dynamics</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://shermanonsoftware.com/2019/11/15/its-not-sabotage-theyre-drowning/\">It's Not Sabotage, They're Drowning</a> - Some kind of push backs shouldn't be interpreted as intentional sabotage, but as drowning people sinking the lifeboat in an attempt to save themselves.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Remote Work</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://increment.com/teams/a-guide-to-distributed-teams/\">A guide to distributed teams</a> - A nice wrap up on the numerous dispositions required to have a highly effective distributed team.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Meetings</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://qz.com/work/1713662/how-to-have-great-meetings-according-to-200-scientific-studies/\">How to have great meetings, according to 200 scientific studies</a> - A roadmap for getting meetings right.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Product Management</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/dend/awesome-product-management\">Awesome Product Management</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/dend/awesome-product-management\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">421</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":421,\"repo\":\"dend/awesome-product-management\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A reference. All the missing pieces are found below.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Product Management</h2><h3>Hiring PMs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.venturegrit.com/what-everybody-ought-to-know-about-the-product-manager-case-interview/\">What Everybody Ought To Know About The Product Manager Case Interview</a></li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Product Management</h2><h3>Hiring PMs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.quora.com/What-are-frequently-asked-questions-in-product-manager-interviews\">What are frequently asked questions in product manager interviews?</a></li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Project Management</h2><h3>Estimations</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Escalation_of_commitment\">Escalation of commitment</a> - A.k.a. sunk-cost fallacy, or the rational explanation of why the hell do we still irrationally keep investing in a bad project.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Key Performance Indicator (KPI)</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cloudplatform.googleblog.com/2018/07/sre-fundamentals-slis-slas-and-slos.html\">SRE fundamentals: SLIs, SLAs and SLOs</a> - If you are in the business of cloud services, these metrics are certainly great KPIs.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Key Performance Indicator (KPI)</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.gitclear.com/blog/the_4_worst_software_metrics_agitating_developers_in_2019\">The 4 Worst Software Metrics Agitating Developers in 2019</a> - The worst KPIs to track a software team output: Lines of Code, Commit Count, Issues Resolved (aka “Shipping Velocity”) and Code Churn (aka \"Efficiency\").</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Objectives and Key Results (OKR)</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=17492038\">Google's usage of OKRs</a> - OKR grades are public, but not used for promotion. It was never taken very seriously there.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Training</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://blog.pragmaticengineer.com/developers-mentoring-other-developers/\">Developers mentoring other developers: practices I've seen work well</a> - Discusses mentorship practices that work well engineer-to-engineer.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Training</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://roadmap.sh/roadmaps\">Developer Roadmaps</a> - Very high-level guides and paths to learn different practice and tools.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communication</h2><h3>Reading</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://blizzard.cs.uwaterloo.ca/keshav/home/Papers/data/07/paper-reading.pdf\">How to Read a Paper</a> - Outlines a practical and efficient three-pass method for reading research papers.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communication</h2><h3>Documentation</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.divio.com/blog/documentation/\">What nobody tells you about documentation</a> - There is four kinds of documentation: tutorials, how-to guides, explanation and reference. Each with their own structure and mode of writing.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communication</h2><h3>Documentation</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://flyingcircus.io/doc/reference/security/disaster-recovery.html#disaster-recovery\">Flying Circus Platform - Disaster recovery</a> - Critical infrastructure which aims to be available 24/7 needs a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disaster_recovery\">Disaster Recovery Plan</a>. It generally takes the form of a document providing an overview of the expected severe failures and a set of procedures on how the system and the team operating it is prepared to deal with. The one linked here is a great example of such document, and is strong evidence the team is prepared for the worse.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communication</h2><h3>Writing</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/441f/ac7c2020e1c8f0d32adffca697bbb8a198a1.pdf\">How to Write a Technical Paper</a> - Serves as a guideline on how to write a good technical paper, in the form of a typical journal publication.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communication</h2><h3>Writing</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cs.tufts.edu/~nr/pubs/learn.pdf\">Learning Technical Writing Using the Engineering Method</a> - An alternative approach, involving a weekly meeting of a writing group. An interesting dynamic to gather feedback and experience.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communication</h2><h3>Writing</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://iubmb.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1002/bmb.20329\">Algorithm for writing a scientific manuscript</a> - A process to guide the preparation and refinement of manuscripts.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communication</h2><h3>Writing</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://speakerdeck.com/pycon2016/a-jesse-jiryu-davis-write-an-excellent-programming-blog\">Write an Excellent Programming Blog</a> - Tips on structure and style to produce great blog posts.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communication</h2><h3>Style</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.blablameter.com/\">BlaBlaMeter - Bullshit detection tool</a> - Produce a normalized metric of the bullshit content of a text.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communication</h2><h3>Style</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://marketingbs.whiterhino.com\">Marketing BS Detector</a> - Same as above, but with some tips given.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://larahogan.me/blog/manager-levels/\">Work at different management levels</a> - A great progressive breakup of what it feels like to work at different levels of management.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2><h3>Promotion</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.elidedbranches.com/2017/09/how-do-managers-get-stuck.html\">How do managers get stuck?</a> - Identify scenario preventing managers to be promoted at the next level.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2><h3>Promotion</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://queue.acm.org/detail.cfm?id=3350548\">The Evolution of Management: Transitioning up the ladder</a> - Describe the path and expectations at each management level.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Compensation</h2><h3>Salary</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.levels.fyi\">levels.fyi</a> - Compares salary range and compensation charts across big tech companies.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Politics</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.ribbonfarm.com/the-gervais-principle/\">The Gervais Principle</a> - A cynical, bleak, but still fascinating take on the management ladder, based on <em>The Office</em>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Re-organizations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=17329028\">If I Close My Data Centers, What About the People/Jobs Lost?</a> - F50's data centers being migrated to commercial cloud provider. But what about the people currently doing legacy stuff? The answer: retrain.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Health</h2><h3>Stress</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=21856352\">Examples of harassments</a> - How a jealous boss, who felt either betrayed or ridiculed, bullied a capable employee to force him out. Don't be that kind of asshole boss.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T15:12:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"rust-unofficial/awesome-rust","categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Observability</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Mnwa/gtsa\">Mnwa/gtsa</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Mnwa/gtsa\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">7</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":7,\"repo\":\"Mnwa/gtsa\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> — A simple solution to proxy gelf messages (messages for Graylog) to Sentry</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-15T13:28:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"rust-unofficial/awesome-rust","categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>GUI</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>